GaChalign (ガチャalign) is a python implementation of Gale-Church (1993) sentence aligner with options for variable parameters (viz. mean, variance, penalty).

## FILES
* Test Suites ('ntumc.eng' and 'ntumc.jpn are English and Japanese sentences from NTU-MC; 'eng-jpn.human' are the human-aligned sentences)
* gale-church.py (main module for the algorithm)
* math.py (module if scipy.stats.norm don't import properly)
* GaChalign.pdf (Technical Report for the experiment on English-Japanese alignments with Gale-Church algorithm)

For more details, see http://code.google.com/p/gachalign/



